news.title: Centre reimposes GRAP 3 curbs as air quality worsens in Delhi-NCR
news.para: Delhi's air pollution levels showed an increasing trend and the 24-hour average air quality index (AQI) stood at 371 at 4 pm.

news.title: Brookfield delays sale of London's Citypoint office tower: Source
news.para: Canadian investor Brookfield had been seeking around 500 million pounds ($620 million) for the 36-storey office tower, but bids came in below 400 million pounds, prompting the owner to pause the sales process, the source told Reuters.

news.title: Kolkata: NKDA plans crackdown on residential buildings violating commercial-use rule
news.para: Officials said the authorities had been receiving complaints from different quarters over such rampant use of residential space for commercial purposes, and local residents had been complaining about loud noise and music coming from these houses till late at night.

news.title: Yusen Logistics leases two lakh sq ft warehouse from Macrotech Developers in Palava
news.para: The built-to-suit facility is part of Lodha Industrial & Logistics Parks (LILP) and is strategically chosen to enhance the Tokyo-headquartered company’s distribution network in India.

news.title: Brigade Group acquires 20 acres land in Bengaluru for Rs 630 crore
news.para: Brigade Group's residential project will have a total saleable area of approximately 2.5 million sq ft and a gross development value (GDV) of about Rs 2,700 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt launches online survey for transparent beneficiary selection in PMAY
news.para: The survey will be facilitated through the recently launched Awas Plus App, designed to ensure transparency in the selection of beneficiaries while simplifying the process of providing housing under the scheme.

news.title: Maharashtra deputy CM directs officials to come up with 'housing for all' policy
news.para: Shinde, who holds the housing and urban development department, also asked officials to clear impediments in the redevelopment of housing projects in Mumbai which have been stuck for various reasons.

news.title: Noida authority to allow registry of properties transferred through multiple GPAs
news.para: The proposed policy, officials said, aims to not only legitimise property ownership but also recover revenue that the Authority and state govt lost over the years in the absence of any such rule.

news.title: Greater Noida authority offers 10 residential plots through e-auction
news.para: The allocation of these plots will be done through e-auction, and possession of the plots will be handed over within 30 days of completing formalities.

news.title: Nashik: Mhada to allot 555 flats for EWS in nine residential projects
news.para: In Nov 2013, state govt had made it mandatory for builders and developers to reserve 20% flats for the low-income group in residential projects spanning across 4,000sqm or above in cities with a population of more than 10 lakh.

news.title: Gujarat CM urges builders to submit feedback on new jantri rates
news.para: The CM inaugurated the Credai Ahmedabad Property Show 2025 and asked developers to ensure that buyers benefit from schemes provided by the govt.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates several development projects in Delhi
news.para: Prime Minister Narendra Modi handed over the keys to eligible beneficiaries of EWS flats at Swabhiman Apartments in the Ashok Vihar area.

news.title: India’s office sector sees 89 million sq ft leasing this year: Cushman & Wakefield
news.para: Bengaluru led the charge, accounting for 29% of India’s gross leasing volume (25.93 million sq ft), followed by Mumbai at 20% (17.84 million sq ft) and Delhi-NCR at 15% (13.14 million sq ft).

news.title: Norway's sovereign wealth fund acquires 45% stake in US logistics properties for $1.07 billion
news.para: Norges Bank Investment Management (NBIM), the world's largest sovereign wealth fund, said it valued the portfolio at $3.27 billion, which is encumbered by $888 million of existing debt.

news.title: Trichy corporation to expand by merging 22 panchayats
news.para: While a total of 25 panchayats were considered initially, the municipal administration department passed an order finalising 20 panchayats for a complete merger and two panchayats for partial merger based on the urbanization level.

news.title: Telangana HC orders disciplinary action against revenue officials over land acquisition delay
news.para: Disciplinary action against revenue officials concerned for being complacent in acquiring land for the construction of Shivanna Gudem balancing reservoir at Khudabakshpally village, Marriguda mandal, Nalgonda district.

news.title: Property developer booked for duping Bihar woman of Rs 42 lakh
news.para: Dr Rashmi Kumari from Bihar's Sheikhpura had paid the money for a house and a land parcel in Lucknow but the deal turned out to be a scam, they said.

news.title: Right to property a constitutional right: Supreme court
news.para: A bench of justices B R Gavai and K V Viswanathan said the right to property ceased to be a fundamental right due to the Constitution (Forty-Fourth Amendment) Act, 1978, however, it continues to be a human right in a welfare state and a constitutional right under Article 300-A of the Constitution.

news.title: Gujarat: District collectors assigned to oversee administration of nine new municipal corporations
news.para: According to a Press release, with these Municipal Corporations becoming effective immediately, their existing administrative structures will be replaced, and the respective District Collectors will assume the role of Administrators for these Corporations.

news.title: Jaipur development body removes encroachment from 40 bighas of government land
news.para: Deputy inspector general of police in JDA, Kailash Chandra Bishnoi, said, "On learning that about 40 bighas of JDA-owned govt land meant for group housing scheme was encroached upon by local farmers, action was taken Thursday.
